MELBOURNE- Australia's Pilbara Ports Authority (PPA) said on Wednesday that throughput slipped 1% in April from year earlier. April's throughput was 58.8-million tonnes, the PPA said in a statement. Iron ore exports from Port Hedland were 41.8-million tonnes, the statement said. That is up 15% from March when iron ore shipments from Australia were disrupted due to the impact of Cyclone Veronica.